ref=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">G</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Quotient.html#HasQuotient.Quotient\">⧸</a> <span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/InfiniteSum/Module.html#QuotientGroup.automorphize\">automorphize</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Map.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.map\">MeasureTheory.Measure.map</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/Coset/Defs.html#QuotientGroup.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Restrict.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.restrict\">restrict</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This is a simple version of the **Unfolding Trick**: Given a subgroup `Γ` of a group `G`, the\nintegral of a function `f` on `G` with respect to a right-invariant measure `μ` is equal to the\nintegral over the quotient `G ⧸ Γ` of the automorphization of `f`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.html#QuotientGroup.integral_eq_integral_automorphize","kind":"theorem","line":380,"name":"QuotientGroup.integral_eq_integral_automorphize","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.lean#L380-L399"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.html#MeasureTheory.IsAddFundamentalDomain.absolutelyContinuous_map\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>