an class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Map.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.map\">Measure.map</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/Coset/Defs.html#QuotientGroup.mk\">QuotientGroup.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.AbsolutelyContinuous\">AbsolutelyContinuous</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Map.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.map\">Measure.map</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/Coset/Defs.html#QuotientGroup.mk\">QuotientGroup.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Restrict.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.restrict\">restrict</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a quotient space `G ⧸ Γ` where `Γ` is `Countable`, and the restriction,\n`μ_𝓕`, of a right-invariant measure `μ` on `G` to a fundamental domain `𝓕`, a set\nin the quotient which has `μ_𝓕`-measure zero, also has measure zero under the\nfolding of `μ` under the quotient. Note that, if `Γ` is infinite, then the folded map\nwill take the value `∞` on any open set in the quotient! ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.html#MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.absolutelyContinuous_map","kind":"theorem","line":351,"name":"MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.absolutelyContinuous_map","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.lean#L351-L376"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.html#essSup_comp_quotientAddGroup_mk\"><span class=\"name\">essSup_comp_quotientAddGroup_mk</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">