s=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">ν</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">V</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> (<span class=\"fn\">G</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Quotient.html#HasQuotient.Quotient\">⧸</a> <span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">meas_V</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSet\">MeasurableSet</a> <span class=\"fn\">V</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">neZeroV</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">V</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hV</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">V</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ν</span> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/Coset/Defs.html#QuotientGroup.mk\">QuotientGroup.mk</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <span class=\"fn\">V</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Inter.inter\">∩</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">neTopV</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">V</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Group/FundamentalDomain.html#MeasureTheory.QuotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage\">QuotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage</a> <span class=\"fn\">ν</span> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Assume that a measure `μ` is `IsMulLeftInvariant`, that the action of `Γ` on `G` has a\nmeasurable fundamental domain `s` with positive finite volume, and that there is a single measurable\nset `V ⊆ G ⧸ Γ` along which the pullback of `μ` and `ν` agree (so the scaling is right). Then\n`μ` satisfies `QuotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage`. The main tool of the proof is the uniqueness of\nleft invariant measures, if normalized by a single positive finite-measured set. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.IsMulLeftInvariant.quotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage_of_set","kind":"theorem","line":149,"name":"MeasureTheory.Measure.IsMulLeftInvariant.quotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage_of_set","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.lean#L149-L184"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/Quotient.html#MeasureTheory.AddQuotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage.addInvariantMeasure_quotient\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">AddQuotientMeasureEqMeasurePreimage</span>.<span class=\"name\">addInvariantMeasure_quotient</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddGroup\">AddGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></sp